T1  - The Threat of Unionization, the Use of Debt, and the Preservation of Shareholder Wealth*
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937914
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 106
IS  - 1
SP  - 231
EP  - 254
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper argues that firms use debt to protect the wealth of shareholders from the threat of unionization. Under U. S. labor law the firm cannot prohibit its workers from attempting to form a collective bargaining unit. Debt policy offers a method of reducing the impact of this monopoly right on shareholders. By issuing debt, the firm credibly reduces the funds that are available to a potential union. Empirical evidence that strongly supports this hypothesis is presented.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937914
ER  - 



